group_by_taxlevel <- function(taxlevel, data = nonOyster20_wm %>% filter(Info1 %in% c("Crash", "Good"))){
  taxlevelQ <- enquo(taxlevel)
  data %>%
    group_by(Sample, `Brood#`, DayN, Type, Info1, Info2, "Taxid" = rlang::eval_tidy(sym(taxlevel))) %>%
    summarise(ratio = sum(ratio), n = n()) %>%
    ungroup()
}

testGrp <- group_by_taxlevel("Tag_ASV")
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'Sample', 'Brood#', 'DayN', 'Type', 'Info1', 'Info2'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
